parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and cracks can cause fuel vapors to fill the cabin, posing a risk of fire and intoxicating fumes, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: difficulty starting the engine when cold
fuel leaks stopping when the engine warms up.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leaks around Clamped Rubber Hoses in Intake Manifold
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks around the intake manifold can cause a strong fuel smell in the cabin, which can lead to nausea, fogging of interior windows, and potentially, a fire hazard.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell in the cabin
fuel leaks from clamped rubber hoses in the intake manifold
fuel smell persisting even after the vehicle has warmed up.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Replacement Parts for Takata Airbag Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts for the Takata airbag recall can leave vehicles without functional passenger airbags, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: uncertainty about the safety of the vehicle.
